# .semgrepignore — permanent file-glob exclusions for the pen-test gate.
#
# This is for files that are PERMANENTLY out of scope for the custom ruleset
# (generated code, vendored deps, test fixtures). Pre-existing findings in
# in-scope code are NOT listed here — those are grandfathered automatically by
# diff-only scanning (--baseline-commit in scripts/pentest-review.sh), so they
# never block while any NEW finding does.
#
# Each entry carries a `# reason:` so a reviewer can audit why. ADR-027.

# reason: generated from api/openapi.yaml; hand-edits are overwritten. The
#         spec-drift check (Rule 6) covers the YAML source of truth instead.
server/internal/api/openapi_gen.go
*_gen.go
*.pb.go

# reason: generated TypeScript API types (npm run generate:api).
web/src/types/api.d.ts

# reason: test code exercises adversarial shapes deliberately (fixtures,
#         negative-path assertions); scanning it produces noise, not signal.
*_test.go
*.test.ts
*.test.tsx
*.spec.ts
**/tests/**
**/__tests__/**
**/e2e/**

# reason: vendored / third-party — not our code to gate.
node_modules/
**/target/**
vendor/

# reason: the pen-test test harness creates intentionally-vulnerable ephemeral
#         fixtures; never scan them in a real run.
scripts/tests/
